{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, in order to add 'cholesterol' to the vocabulary, we need to add one extra token [chole].",
    "Specifically, for Llama-3.1, we observe an overall addition of 20% of extra such tokens, which are seldom used once the complete word is added into the vocabulary.",
    "This can lead to reduced performance in downstream tasks.",
    "To that end, we present Scaf-Fix to address this issue with existing vocabulary adaptation strategies.",
    "Unlike the vocabulary adaptation strategies described till now, ScafFix constructs the candidate set for added vocabulary by directly considering the medical words and ignores the tokenization step for forming candidate subwords."
  ]
}